# Event-Driven Todo (local-first, CQRS + Event Sourcing)
 
A small Go todo application demonstrating **CQRS** and **event sourcing** with an
event-driven write→read loop, running entirely locally — no cloud account, no
authentication. Postgres is the event store and read model; the Google Pub/Sub
emulator is the message bus.
 
The read model is fully derived from an append-only event log and can be
reconstructed from scratch at any time (`POST /admin/rebuild`), which is the
defining property of event sourcing: **events are the only source of truth.**

## Architecture
 
The system separates the **write side** (commands that produce events) from the
**read side** (queries that serve a denormalized projection). They never touch
each other's tables; the message bus is the only link between them.

## API
 
```
POST   /todos                     create a todo            201 {"id": "..."}
POST   /todos/{id}/complete       mark a todo done         202
GET    /todos                     list todos (newest first) 200 [ ... ]
GET    /todos/{id}                get one todo             200 | 404
POST   /events                    Pub/Sub push target       (internal)
POST   /admin/rebuild             replay events → read model 200 {"events_applied": N}
GET    /healthz                   liveness                  200 ok
```


## Run it
 
```sh
cp .env.example .env
make up                       # Postgres + Pub/Sub emulator, waits until healthy
make migrate-up               # creates events + todos_read
 
set -a; source .env; set +a   # export env (PUBSUB_EMULATOR_HOST etc.) for the app
make run                      # starts the server on :8080
```



## Try the full loop
 
```sh
# create
ID=$(curl -s -X POST localhost:8080/todos -d '{"title":"buy milk"}' | jq -r .id)
sleep 1
curl -s localhost:8080/todos | jq          # the todo appears (via the projection)
 
# complete
curl -s -X POST localhost:8080/todos/$ID/complete
sleep 1
curl -s localhost:8080/todos/$ID | jq      # done: true
 
# prove the read model is disposable: wipe it, then rebuild from events
docker exec todo-postgres psql -U todo -d todo -c "TRUNCATE todos_read"
curl -s localhost:8080/todos | jq          # []  — empty
curl -s -X POST localhost:8080/admin/rebuild | jq   # {"events_applied": N}
curl -s localhost:8080/todos | jq          # fully reconstructed from the event log
```

## How they work together
User POST /todos
    ↓
command.go (validates, creates event)
    ↓
store.go (saves to events table)
    ↓
pubsub.go (publishes event)
    ↓
Pub/Sub delivers to POST /events
    ↓
projection.go (receives event)
    ↓
store.go (updates todos_read table)
    ↓
User GET /todos
    ↓
query.go (reads from todos_read)
    ↓
User sees their todo